[thinking] **Considering native compilation**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about whether the native compilation process is automatic for native builds. Typically, the GraalVM native plugin agent runs JVM tests first, creating configurations in `build/native/agent-output/test`, which the nativeCompile uses. I guess in the TCK it might work that way, but for the final committed version, it really should operate in a fresh native environment. This seems crucial to ensure everything functions as expected!
[thinking] 
