[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about whether I can create a test class under `src/test/java/org/apache/logging/log4j` that uses Logger/LogManager/Level. It seems like there’s a guideline to keep tests outside the library’s packages, which is related to HSQLDB. Stubbing external packages could be a bit questionable. I’m also wondering about the structure – should there be one-to-one active classes and are additional helper classes allowed? Would they need to be public or could they just be package-private? This feels a bit complicated!
